1
00:00:09,223 --> 00:00:11,357
[ music playing ]

2
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:15,128
[ waves crashing ]

3
00:00:39,637 --> 00:00:42,355
[ birds chirping ]

4
00:00:42,423 --> 00:00:43,657
[ gasps ]

5
00:00:55,786 --> 00:00:56,819
[ groans ]

6
00:01:06,130 --> 00:01:08,799
[ panting ]

7
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:27,033
[ gasps ]

8
00:02:51,369 --> 00:02:53,686
[ waterfall rushing ]

9
00:03:22,783 --> 00:03:24,634
[ panting ]

10
00:03:41,853 --> 00:03:44,570
[ stereo playing rock-'n'-roll ]

11
00:03:47,658 --> 00:03:50,626
Excuse me.
Have you seen this woman?

12
00:03:50,694 --> 00:03:51,545
No.

13
00:03:51,612 --> 00:03:53,713
Have you seen this woman?

14
00:03:53,915 --> 00:03:56,332
How 'bout this man here?

15
00:03:56,534 --> 00:03:58,151
Hey, if I were you,

16
00:03:58,536 --> 00:03:59,886
I'd take
those photographs,

17
00:03:59,954 --> 00:04:01,821
and I'd leave.

18
00:04:01,889 --> 00:04:04,157
All right.

19
00:04:04,224 --> 00:04:06,926
[ music playing in Spanish ]

20
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:29,049
[ woman gasping ]

21
00:04:31,051 --> 00:04:32,819
Wait! Wait!

22
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:41,361
Wait, wait!
[ gasps ]

23
00:04:41,429 --> 00:04:44,163
Please wait.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

24
00:04:44,231 --> 00:04:46,917
No, stop! Stop! No!

25
00:04:48,568 --> 00:04:49,836
[ yells ]
MAN: No, no, no! Todd!

26
00:04:49,904 --> 00:04:51,237
Todd! Todd! Todd!
She's good.

27
00:04:51,305 --> 00:04:52,555
She's good.
Shit, we gotta go.

28
00:04:52,623 --> 00:04:54,524
Come on! Come on.
Come on! Move!

29
00:05:00,547 --> 00:05:02,516
Come on! Come on!

30
00:05:08,689 --> 00:05:10,089
Erin!

31
00:05:10,157 --> 00:05:11,240
I think we have--

32
00:05:11,308 --> 00:05:13,176
Erin, stop!
Come on!

33
00:05:15,763 --> 00:05:18,164
Wait! What the hell
is going on here?

34
00:05:18,232 --> 00:05:19,965
Wait. Another one?
Yeah, yeah.

35
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:22,118
What do you mean another one?
Who are you people?

36
00:05:22,185 --> 00:05:24,354
They're bad. We have to go.
Where am I?

37
00:05:24,421 --> 00:05:25,788
Follow us. Come on!

38
00:05:41,138 --> 00:05:42,105
[ sparks crackle ]

39
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,247
[ screams ]

40
00:05:56,653 --> 00:05:58,488
There you go.
Jeez.

41
00:05:58,555 --> 00:05:59,705
What'd she fall, three feet?

42
00:05:59,773 --> 00:06:01,441
Bitch has been pretzeled.

43
00:06:01,575 --> 00:06:03,626
Think she'll live?

44
00:06:03,694 --> 00:06:04,544
No.

45
00:06:09,099 --> 00:06:10,633
[ shallow breathing ]

46
00:06:15,055 --> 00:06:16,472
[ panting ]

47
00:06:18,959 --> 00:06:20,694
Okay, sweetheart, listen to me.

48
00:06:20,761 --> 00:06:22,279
We'll get you out of here.

49
00:06:22,346 --> 00:06:24,697
It's gonna be on a boat.
It's gonna be very choppy.

50
00:06:24,765 --> 00:06:26,983
I'm not sure if you'll be able
to take the pain.

51
00:06:28,802 --> 00:06:32,038
Give me a blink if you want me
to stop the pain.

52
00:06:33,724 --> 00:06:36,175
Give me a blink, sweetheart.

53
00:06:37,444 --> 00:06:38,811
[ neck cracks ]
All right.

54
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:42,198
Let's get her out of here
while she's still warm.

55
00:06:48,706 --> 00:06:50,039
[ gasps ]

56
00:06:50,107 --> 00:06:51,124
Shh, shh. Shh.

57
00:06:53,644 --> 00:06:56,495
[ sobbing ]

58
00:06:56,563 --> 00:06:57,897
What the hell was that?

59
00:06:57,964 --> 00:07:01,417
Every few days,
they take someone new.

60
00:07:01,485 --> 00:07:03,052
Where do they take them?

61
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,621
We don't know, but if you want
to survive out here,

62
00:07:05,689 --> 00:07:07,123
you have to talk to Quentin.

63
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:08,558
And this Quentin,

64
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:10,393
he knows why we're here?

65
00:07:10,460 --> 00:07:12,178
You can ask him yourself.

66
00:07:12,246 --> 00:07:14,063
Let's go.

67
00:07:14,131 --> 00:07:15,648
Come on.

68
00:07:31,365 --> 00:07:33,466
[ beeping ]

69
00:07:44,578 --> 00:07:45,645
What you got for me?

70
00:07:45,712 --> 00:07:47,097
Got a call
from Nikolai in Kiev.

71
00:07:47,231 --> 00:07:49,065
Nothing bad.
He said he's very pleased,

72
00:07:49,216 --> 00:07:52,251
and he has some other business
he'd like to send our way.

73
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:53,737
That is excellent news.

74
00:07:53,804 --> 00:07:58,341
Also our friend from the east
is coming tomorrow.

75
00:07:58,409 --> 00:08:00,126
Mao? Okay.

76
00:08:00,194 --> 00:08:02,796
Well, then I guess let's make
sure that there's a room prepared.

77
00:08:02,863 --> 00:08:05,899
Mao's not coming alone.

78
00:08:07,118 --> 00:08:08,518
Okay. Well, then I guess

79
00:08:08,585 --> 00:08:12,222
we'll have to make sure that
there are more rooms prepared.

80
00:08:18,629 --> 00:08:20,196
Hey, Chloe.

81
00:08:20,264 --> 00:08:21,530
Where's Erin?

82
00:08:21,598 --> 00:08:22,949
She's gone.

83
00:08:23,017 --> 00:08:24,300
What?

84
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:26,703
No, no, no, no! Hey!

85
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:28,804
Chloe, where's Erin?!

86
00:08:28,872 --> 00:08:30,990
Hi.

87
00:08:31,608 --> 00:08:33,676
I love you.

88
00:08:39,466 --> 00:08:40,132
What the hell happened?

89
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,484
They came out of nowhere,

90
00:08:41,552 --> 00:08:42,618
and we got separated.

91
00:08:42,686 --> 00:08:44,036
You're not supposed to separate!

92
00:08:51,112 --> 00:08:52,345
Interesting.

93
00:08:52,412 --> 00:08:54,413
One gets taken.

94
00:08:54,481 --> 00:08:56,098
Another one shows up.

95
00:09:02,473 --> 00:09:04,374
What's your name?

96
00:09:05,493 --> 00:09:07,159
Billie,

97
00:09:07,227 --> 00:09:08,828
Billie Kope.

98
00:09:11,799 --> 00:09:13,400
I'm Quentin.

99
00:09:16,287 --> 00:09:18,237
You can have that hut there.

100
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:21,474
It was Erin's.

101
00:09:23,010 --> 00:09:25,311
There are some rules you'll
have to hear

102
00:09:25,378 --> 00:09:27,063
before you settle in.

103
00:09:27,131 --> 00:09:28,131
Mr. Quentin!

104
00:09:29,016 --> 00:09:31,317
Thank you so much
for the hospitality,

105
00:09:31,384 --> 00:09:33,453
but I never said I was staying.

106
00:09:34,705 --> 00:09:35,505
You don't have to.

107
00:09:35,573 --> 00:09:36,956
We don't
hold hostages here.

108
00:09:37,024 --> 00:09:40,026
Who were those people
that came after us?

109
00:09:41,245 --> 00:09:43,696
I've got some ideas.

110
00:09:43,964 --> 00:09:45,148
Join us for dinner.

111
00:10:02,283 --> 00:10:03,382
So, Ms. Kope...

112
00:10:04,651 --> 00:10:05,435
what's your story?

113
00:10:05,502 --> 00:10:07,520
Tell us how you got here.

114
00:10:07,587 --> 00:10:09,389
You first.

115
00:10:10,457 --> 00:10:14,244
Heh. They've all heard my story.

116
00:10:14,311 --> 00:10:18,848
You'll find that a lot of the
circumstances are the same.

117
00:10:21,352 --> 00:10:23,186
Yeah, I won a sweepstakes.

118
00:10:23,254 --> 00:10:24,286
[ chuckles ]

119
00:10:25,422 --> 00:10:27,790
Visit paradise. Heh.

120
00:10:32,997 --> 00:10:35,548
The last thing I remember, I was
at a bar in Guatemala.

121
00:10:35,616 --> 00:10:37,717
I was supposed to meet with this
crazy witch doctor dude.

122
00:10:37,785 --> 00:10:41,170
He was gonna get me these
German expats on how to make ayahuasca.

123
00:10:41,238 --> 00:10:42,605
What's ayahuasca?

124
00:10:42,672 --> 00:10:43,973
That's hippie shit.

125
00:10:45,443 --> 00:10:47,343
You got a closed mind, Todd.

126
00:10:47,411 --> 00:10:48,344
No, it's not.

127
00:10:49,413 --> 00:10:50,947
I never got to try it.

128
00:10:51,848 --> 00:10:53,916
[ sighs ]
I was in a bar

129
00:10:53,984 --> 00:10:56,218
drinking some tequila.

130
00:10:56,286 --> 00:10:59,405
Next thing you know, right here,
paradise.

131
00:10:59,473 --> 00:11:00,840
It was about a week ago.

132
00:11:00,907 --> 00:11:02,808
I been here about five days.

133
00:11:02,876 --> 00:11:05,878
I was doing a presentation
in Caracas,

134
00:11:05,945 --> 00:11:07,714
and my head felt weird.

135
00:11:07,781 --> 00:11:09,565
My stomach was hurting.

136
00:11:09,633 --> 00:11:11,333
I thought I had food poisoning,

137
00:11:11,401 --> 00:11:14,120
went to the doctor,
checked on my vital. It was good,

138
00:11:14,188 --> 00:11:16,806
so I went back to the hotel.
Then I passed out.

139
00:11:17,108 --> 00:11:18,291
Then, boom, I am here.

140
00:11:18,358 --> 00:11:20,843
I felt like someone hit me
over the head

141
00:11:20,911 --> 00:11:22,145
with a baseball bat.

142
00:11:22,213 --> 00:11:24,147
I don't remember anything else.

143
00:11:25,783 --> 00:11:27,150
Your turn, Ms. Kope.

144
00:11:29,486 --> 00:11:31,237
Tell us your story.

145
00:11:38,095 --> 00:11:41,914
Have you seen this man?
Do you know him?

146
00:11:43,284 --> 00:11:44,583
No,

147
00:11:44,651 --> 00:11:46,986
but I know someone who does.

148
00:11:50,524 --> 00:11:52,174
Come on.

149
00:12:12,129 --> 00:12:14,597
Look, I don't have anything.

150
00:12:15,633 --> 00:12:17,650
I have no money, nothing, okay?

151
00:12:17,718 --> 00:12:18,984
[ chuckles ]

152
00:12:22,355 --> 00:12:23,606
Catch!

153
00:12:39,856 --> 00:12:41,124
[ blade scrapes ]

154
00:12:48,248 --> 00:12:49,314
[ laughs ]

155
00:12:49,382 --> 00:12:50,566
[ groans ]

156
00:12:59,944 --> 00:13:01,493
[ bone cracks ]
[ yells ]

157
00:13:15,709 --> 00:13:17,226
[ bone cracks ]

158
00:13:28,672 --> 00:13:30,740
[ gasps ]

159
00:13:31,658 --> 00:13:34,543
I guess just like you guys,

160
00:13:34,611 --> 00:13:36,879
I went out to a bar,

161
00:13:36,947 --> 00:13:38,981
I came home...

162
00:13:40,817 --> 00:13:43,352
and the next thing I remember,

163
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:45,154
I woke up here.

164
00:13:55,015 --> 00:13:57,249
Why don't we all, uh...

165
00:13:58,752 --> 00:14:02,188
have a moment of silence
for Erin?

166
00:14:27,331 --> 00:14:29,949
Walsh, look alive.
We got incoming.

167
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:42,461
Jesus Christ, what happened?

168
00:14:43,079 --> 00:14:45,031
Occupational hazard.

169
00:14:45,098 --> 00:14:47,015
You killed her?!

170
00:14:47,885 --> 00:14:49,418
She did it to herself.

171
00:14:49,486 --> 00:14:50,235
Yeah, right.

172
00:14:50,303 --> 00:14:53,222
Cut the bullshit.
What happened?

173
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:54,840
I don't know. Why?
Is there a problem?

174
00:14:54,908 --> 00:14:57,893
Rich, I need you to go over
the stuff for Mao's visit.

175
00:14:57,961 --> 00:14:59,195
Mao's coming? When?

176
00:14:59,262 --> 00:15:00,997
Tomorrow, so be ready.

177
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,784
Walsh, what do you think?

178
00:15:04,851 --> 00:15:06,185
She's still warm.

179
00:15:06,253 --> 00:15:08,587
Gotta get her on the table
and look inside.

180
00:15:08,655 --> 00:15:11,490
If she's not past
her expiration date, then we're good.

181
00:15:11,558 --> 00:15:13,692
Xander, you were there.
What happened?

182
00:15:15,145 --> 00:15:16,712
It's like the Sarge said.

183
00:15:16,779 --> 00:15:18,647
Cut the bullshit.

184
00:15:18,715 --> 00:15:19,965
What happened?

185
00:15:22,836 --> 00:15:25,605
Look, I was
running after her.

186
00:15:25,672 --> 00:15:27,640
I took the shot.
I missed.

187
00:15:27,707 --> 00:15:30,009
She took off.
She fell,

188
00:15:30,076 --> 00:15:32,345
broke her neck.

189
00:15:37,501 --> 00:15:40,302
All right, get her inside.
Hurry.

190
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:47,609
[ birds warbling,
insects chirping ]

191
00:15:51,981 --> 00:15:55,317
Hey, Billie.

192
00:15:55,385 --> 00:15:57,119
Billie.

193
00:15:57,187 --> 00:15:58,587
Hey, listen.

194
00:15:58,655 --> 00:16:01,957
I know you're, like, freaked out
and stuff, right?

195
00:16:02,025 --> 00:16:03,125
I got your back, baby.

196
00:16:03,193 --> 00:16:04,293
I'll protect you.

197
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,662
I swear to God
I'm so good at that.

198
00:16:06,730 --> 00:16:09,432
I'm good, thank you.

199
00:16:13,536 --> 00:16:15,705
[ sighs ]

200
00:16:20,994 --> 00:16:22,177
Billie.

201
00:16:24,781 --> 00:16:27,483
You know
what sounds good?

202
00:16:27,551 --> 00:16:30,019
Like, a bike ride...

203
00:16:30,086 --> 00:16:33,622
and a nice cup of coffee.

204
00:16:34,575 --> 00:16:37,860
If you need, like, a shoulder
to lean on,

205
00:16:37,928 --> 00:16:40,062
I'm really good for that, too.

206
00:16:42,699 --> 00:16:43,933
Th-Thank you.

207
00:16:44,001 --> 00:16:47,119
And then cuddling naked.

208
00:16:51,624 --> 00:16:53,458
[ sighs ]

209
00:17:00,967 --> 00:17:03,619
Jean, how long
have you been here?

210
00:17:03,687 --> 00:17:05,004
10 days.

211
00:17:05,072 --> 00:17:06,388
And how'd you get here?

212
00:17:06,457 --> 00:17:08,423
I went to San José,
Costa Rica,

213
00:17:08,491 --> 00:17:10,860
for my wisdom tooth
to be removed.

214
00:17:10,927 --> 00:17:13,445
I was visiting
friends in Cancún,

215
00:17:13,580 --> 00:17:15,397
and they didn't want
to go out one night,

216
00:17:15,465 --> 00:17:16,966
so I went out by myself.

217
00:17:17,034 --> 00:17:18,951
Do you remember
where you were before?

218
00:17:21,271 --> 00:17:22,672
Were you in prison?

219
00:17:24,074 --> 00:17:27,093
Yeah, I was,
was in a Mexican prison.

220
00:17:28,295 --> 00:17:30,345
It was just an ounce.

221
00:17:30,413 --> 00:17:32,548
Pulled me over at a checkpoint.

222
00:17:34,017 --> 00:17:36,302
They, uh,
searched my car.

223
00:17:36,303 --> 00:17:37,386
It wasn't hidden very well,

224
00:17:37,454 --> 00:17:38,620
and the rest is history.

225
00:17:38,805 --> 00:17:40,956
Somebody must have slipped
something in my drink,

226
00:17:41,024 --> 00:17:42,291
'cause I started
seeing spots.

227
00:17:42,358 --> 00:17:46,011
They, uh, took me
to this prison doctor,

228
00:17:46,079 --> 00:17:49,215
and he runs, you know,
test after test on me.

229
00:17:49,282 --> 00:17:51,400
I took a cab back home.

230
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:54,370
I went back to my cell
to sleep, and...

231
00:17:54,438 --> 00:17:57,256
I went back to my hotel...

232
00:17:57,324 --> 00:18:00,092
And I woke up here.

233
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:03,111
So you go to sleep in
a Mexican prison

234
00:18:03,179 --> 00:18:05,681
and then wake up here?

235
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:07,883
Yeah.

236
00:18:13,006 --> 00:18:17,243
Is there anywhere I can get a
full view of this island?

237
00:18:17,311 --> 00:18:19,245
Yeah, it's through this way.

238
00:18:22,015 --> 00:18:24,250
You know,
both Berto and Todd

239
00:18:24,318 --> 00:18:27,686
saw the doctor
before they came here.

240
00:18:27,754 --> 00:18:30,423
Yeah, but, uh, Todd was
from Venezuela,

241
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:33,826
and, uh,
Berto was in Mexico.

242
00:18:33,893 --> 00:18:38,030
So what? Still could be some
connection here.

243
00:18:38,098 --> 00:18:39,498
Even Jean had
been to a dentist.

244
00:18:39,633 --> 00:18:41,918
Had you been to a doctor
before you came here?

245
00:18:41,985 --> 00:18:43,069
Actually, I did.

246
00:18:43,136 --> 00:18:45,804
I got blood work done
in Guatemala City,

247
00:18:45,872 --> 00:18:47,006
malaria test.

248
00:18:47,074 --> 00:18:48,591
Did you have malaria?

249
00:18:48,658 --> 00:18:50,659
No, I'm actually perfectly healthy.

250
00:18:52,195 --> 00:18:55,497
Okay, so all of you have been
to a doctor

251
00:18:55,565 --> 00:18:59,068
and had some kind of
blood work done.

252
00:18:59,136 --> 00:18:59,818
What about you?

253
00:19:01,054 --> 00:19:02,872
No.

254
00:19:03,974 --> 00:19:06,391
How did you know
Berto was in prison?

255
00:19:07,194 --> 00:19:08,677
Lucky guess.

256
00:19:10,530 --> 00:19:13,098
Can I ask you something?
What?

257
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,284
Have you been in prison?

258
00:19:17,955 --> 00:19:19,755
No...

259
00:19:19,823 --> 00:19:21,490
you can't ask.

260
00:19:23,060 --> 00:19:25,194
[ announcements
playing in Spanish ]

261
00:19:31,168 --> 00:19:32,517
You must understand

262
00:19:32,585 --> 00:19:35,404
that in this part of the world

263
00:19:35,472 --> 00:19:39,041
people go missing from
the penal system all the time.

264
00:19:39,109 --> 00:19:40,643
Some escape.

265
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:44,046
Others buy their way out.

266
00:19:44,114 --> 00:19:45,314
But for your sister,

267
00:19:45,382 --> 00:19:48,284
I'm afraid it may be
something different.

268
00:19:49,186 --> 00:19:52,187
For instance,
someone like yourself,

269
00:19:52,255 --> 00:19:54,957
young woman, attractive,

270
00:19:55,025 --> 00:19:56,608
someone like that,

271
00:19:56,676 --> 00:19:58,610
sometimes...

272
00:19:58,678 --> 00:19:59,711
get sold.

273
00:20:00,864 --> 00:20:02,064
Sold?

274
00:20:02,132 --> 00:20:04,566
Sold to who?

275
00:20:06,302 --> 00:20:09,338
Wait. I need to know
who buys prisoners.

276
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,456
Lower your voice.

277
00:20:12,225 --> 00:20:14,710
I need to know
who bought my sister.

278
00:20:16,763 --> 00:20:17,896
Please.

279
00:20:19,132 --> 00:20:22,301
Okay. I'll do
what I can to help.

280
00:20:24,304 --> 00:20:25,771
And, please,
for your safety,

281
00:20:25,838 --> 00:20:28,641
don't go around asking about
these people,

282
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:32,094
or you may find yourself
vanishing, too.

283
00:20:49,979 --> 00:20:51,764
Hey, look. There.

284
00:20:51,832 --> 00:20:53,782
Another island.

285
00:20:54,501 --> 00:20:56,285
We need to get there.

286
00:20:56,353 --> 00:20:58,287
Oh, no, Billie, Billie,
like, that--

287
00:20:58,355 --> 00:21:00,222
that island
is five miles off.

288
00:21:00,423 --> 00:21:02,007
That's five miles of
ocean currents.

289
00:21:02,074 --> 00:21:03,575
You get knocked off course,

290
00:21:03,643 --> 00:21:06,878
you're gonna be 20 miles out
before you know what happened.

291
00:21:06,946 --> 00:21:08,313
So what do you suggest,

292
00:21:08,381 --> 00:21:09,615
staying here
and waiting to die?

293
00:21:09,649 --> 00:21:11,249
I'm just saying,
if it was that easy,

294
00:21:11,317 --> 00:21:13,235
don't you think we would have
already swam there?

295
00:21:13,303 --> 00:21:15,137
How can you say
something can't be done

296
00:21:15,205 --> 00:21:16,188
until you actually try it?

297
00:21:16,255 --> 00:21:18,374
So you gonna swim there?

298
00:21:20,226 --> 00:21:22,060
I didn't say that.

299
00:21:22,128 --> 00:21:23,128
Come on.

300
00:21:30,654 --> 00:21:31,554
Good.

301
00:21:31,621 --> 00:21:34,206
There's plenty of wood
for us here.

302
00:21:34,273 --> 00:21:36,341
So we're building a boat?

303
00:21:36,510 --> 00:21:39,361
No, a raft, just enough
to keep us afloat,

304
00:21:39,429 --> 00:21:41,897
and then we'll paddle the rest
of the way.

305
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:46,168
[ whispering ]
Don't move too fast.

306
00:21:46,236 --> 00:21:47,903
There's someone there.

307
00:21:59,366 --> 00:22:01,933
Little birdies left the nest.

308
00:22:03,386 --> 00:22:04,370
What do you want?

309
00:22:04,437 --> 00:22:05,754
Same thing you do,

310
00:22:05,989 --> 00:22:07,539
to get the hell off this island.

311
00:22:07,607 --> 00:22:09,124
How long you been here?

312
00:22:10,927 --> 00:22:13,328
44 days.

313
00:22:13,396 --> 00:22:14,779
Two months?

314
00:22:14,847 --> 00:22:17,032
How did you
survive out here alone?

315
00:22:17,701 --> 00:22:19,218
What I'm trained to do.

316
00:22:19,286 --> 00:22:20,936
What's your background?

317
00:22:22,288 --> 00:22:24,122
S.A.S.,

318
00:22:24,190 --> 00:22:25,707
British special forces.

319
00:22:25,776 --> 00:22:28,177
I was on exercise
on Honduras,

320
00:22:28,245 --> 00:22:29,578
support and training.

321
00:22:29,762 --> 00:22:31,713
Done a tour in Afghanistan.

322
00:22:31,781 --> 00:22:34,266
Injured twice in the surge.

323
00:22:34,334 --> 00:22:36,551
Survival specialist.

324
00:22:37,237 --> 00:22:38,787
How did you get here?

325
00:22:39,805 --> 00:22:41,156
No idea.

326
00:22:41,223 --> 00:22:43,075
Last thing I remember,

327
00:22:43,076 --> 00:22:45,995
I was traveling along
in a transport van.

328
00:22:46,162 --> 00:22:49,631
We got hit.
There was this massive blast.

329
00:22:49,699 --> 00:22:53,452
Then I just heard Miskito
or maybe Spanish.

330
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,387
Anyway, fell unconscious.

331
00:22:55,455 --> 00:22:58,340
Woke up here.

332
00:22:58,407 --> 00:23:00,075
Do you know
why we're here?

333
00:23:00,142 --> 00:23:01,210
Mm-mm.

334
00:23:02,528 --> 00:23:05,213
But together
we could find out.

335
00:23:05,281 --> 00:23:06,348
No way.

336
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:08,400
What if he's one of them,

337
00:23:08,468 --> 00:23:09,401
you know, waiting for us

338
00:23:09,469 --> 00:23:11,337
to lead him back to our camp?

339
00:23:11,404 --> 00:23:13,555
Oh, shush, pretty boy.

340
00:23:13,623 --> 00:23:15,807
I know
where your camp is.

341
00:23:15,875 --> 00:23:17,559
I've been there nights.

342
00:23:17,627 --> 00:23:20,696
I could have
strangled every single one of yez,

343
00:23:20,764 --> 00:23:22,781
but I didn't.

344
00:23:22,848 --> 00:23:25,451
The only person
I wanna kill is them.

345
00:23:25,518 --> 00:23:27,719
You have
my word on that.

346
00:23:30,690 --> 00:23:33,709
There's another island
a few miles away,

347
00:23:33,777 --> 00:23:35,694
and I'm gonna try
and get there,

348
00:23:35,762 --> 00:23:38,413
and any of you who want to get
the hell off this island

349
00:23:38,481 --> 00:23:40,615
can come with me.

350
00:23:40,683 --> 00:23:43,852
You're gonna go with her, Nick,
take a nice swim in the open ocean?

351
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:45,787
We're not swimming.

352
00:23:45,855 --> 00:23:47,339
We're building a raft.

353
00:23:47,406 --> 00:23:48,340
You're building a raft?

354
00:23:48,407 --> 00:23:49,742
Don't you think

355
00:23:49,809 --> 00:23:51,643
I tried everything
to get off this island?

356
00:23:51,710 --> 00:23:52,528
I built a raft.

357
00:23:52,762 --> 00:23:54,629
Plan was to go
to the next island,

358
00:23:54,898 --> 00:23:57,315
that island you're talking about.

359
00:23:57,383 --> 00:23:58,450
If there was no one there,

360
00:23:58,601 --> 00:24:01,370
we'd resupply and
move to the next one.

361
00:24:01,437 --> 00:24:02,688
Oh, we did it.

362
00:24:02,755 --> 00:24:05,524
Except I didn't
factor in a few things.

363
00:24:05,592 --> 00:24:07,443
This island is a seamount.

364
00:24:07,777 --> 00:24:10,312
That means that
once you pass the reef

365
00:24:10,379 --> 00:24:13,949
it drops down 3,000 feet.

366
00:24:15,318 --> 00:24:16,652
Blue water.

367
00:24:16,703 --> 00:24:18,620
There are two things
you have to watch out for.

368
00:24:18,688 --> 00:24:20,973
After the reef,
there are currents

369
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:23,392
that are like the jet stream.
You'll get tossed about.

370
00:24:23,543 --> 00:24:26,879
The raft'll get broken apart to
a million different pieces.

371
00:24:28,347 --> 00:24:31,216
And then the sharks.

372
00:24:32,518 --> 00:24:36,588
You've got mako
and oceanic whitetips.

373
00:24:36,656 --> 00:24:38,790
They call them
wolves of the sea.

374
00:24:39,075 --> 00:24:40,826
We were
two miles offshore

375
00:24:40,893 --> 00:24:43,194
on that nice
little raft we built.

376
00:24:44,563 --> 00:24:48,700
And that's when we
ran aground on the reef.

377
00:24:52,122 --> 00:24:54,990
I'm the only one that
made it out.

378
00:24:57,227 --> 00:25:02,264
So don't tell me about trying to
get off this island, Ms. Kope.

379
00:25:09,372 --> 00:25:11,223
The wolves,

380
00:25:11,290 --> 00:25:13,592
they'll come after you
and show no mercy.

381
00:25:15,528 --> 00:25:16,895
God bless you.

382
00:25:19,766 --> 00:25:21,833
Who's coming with us?

383
00:25:30,192 --> 00:25:31,176
I'm coming.

384
00:25:35,564 --> 00:25:37,916
Now, we're gonna need driftwood.

385
00:25:37,983 --> 00:25:41,386
Look on the coastline.
Jugs, plastic bottles,

386
00:25:41,454 --> 00:25:43,405
whatever shit
people throw away,

387
00:25:43,473 --> 00:25:45,140
that's what
we're gonna use.

388
00:26:07,346 --> 00:26:10,648
So what is it you do again?

389
00:26:10,716 --> 00:26:13,051
I'm a hairdresser.

390
00:26:26,916 --> 00:26:28,583
NICK: If anyone
wants to take a break,

391
00:26:28,651 --> 00:26:31,053
someone should probably
get on top of there.

392
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:33,722
Yeah, Stitch, you're
gonna need a break.

393
00:26:33,790 --> 00:26:35,924
Shut up, man,
Just keep going.

394
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,688
We're almost there.

395
00:26:49,856 --> 00:26:52,140
Nearly there.
Come on. Keep it together.

396
00:27:04,637 --> 00:27:06,071
[ screams ]

397
00:27:08,424 --> 00:27:09,124
Todd?

398
00:27:12,011 --> 00:27:13,612
Oh! There's
a lot of blood!

399
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:16,298
Oh, my God!
Sharks! Sharks!

400
00:28:15,458 --> 00:28:16,825
Hello?

401
00:28:19,695 --> 00:28:22,364
Hello?
Anyone here?

402
00:28:22,432 --> 00:28:23,731
Hello?

403
00:28:23,799 --> 00:28:26,101
Is there someone there?

404
00:28:26,786 --> 00:28:28,836
Hello? Hello?

405
00:28:29,973 --> 00:28:32,057
<i>Necesito teléfono,</i>
<i>por favor.</i>

406
00:28:32,208 --> 00:28:33,308
<i>Sí. No.</i>

407
00:28:35,795 --> 00:28:37,161
Let me check this door.

408
00:28:39,331 --> 00:28:40,832
Excuse me.

409
00:28:42,402 --> 00:28:44,168
Hello?

410
00:28:44,404 --> 00:28:46,337
Can we use your phone to make a call?
Oh, hi.

411
00:28:46,405 --> 00:28:49,340
<i>¡Vayanse aquí!</i>
<i>Llamada la policia.</i>

412
00:28:49,408 --> 00:28:51,426
<i>Llamada</i>
<i>la policia.</i>

413
00:28:51,494 --> 00:28:53,378
<i>Por favor.</i>

414
00:28:54,596 --> 00:28:56,114
Hey! Hey! Come here.

415
00:28:56,181 --> 00:28:57,449
We need your help!
Wait!

416
00:29:01,804 --> 00:29:03,121
Hello? Hi. Sorry.

417
00:29:03,188 --> 00:29:05,306
Hi. Can you please help us?

418
00:29:05,374 --> 00:29:06,508
Hello? Damn it.

419
00:29:06,576 --> 00:29:09,310
What, they don't like Americans
or something?

420
00:29:09,378 --> 00:29:10,779
Nobody likes Americans.

421
00:29:10,847 --> 00:29:12,781
It's not that.
It's something else.

422
00:29:12,849 --> 00:29:14,282
Oh, shit.

423
00:29:22,275 --> 00:29:24,326
4-3-1.

424
00:29:24,394 --> 00:29:25,193
Huh.

425
00:29:25,261 --> 00:29:27,862
Gave up on you a long time ago.

426
00:29:27,930 --> 00:29:29,631
I thought you were dead.

427
00:29:29,698 --> 00:29:30,949
Yeah.

428
00:29:31,017 --> 00:29:33,852
If you and your pussies get rid
of your stun guns,

429
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:35,520
then we'll find out
who's dead.

430
00:29:36,539 --> 00:29:37,989
[ chuckles ]

431
00:29:40,426 --> 00:29:42,110
[ coughs ]

432
00:29:46,766 --> 00:29:48,900
You need to learn some manners.

433
00:29:49,001 --> 00:29:51,453
All yours.

434
00:29:59,662 --> 00:30:03,498
Okay, when you're finished,
bag 'em, and tag 'em.

435
00:30:05,201 --> 00:30:07,636
[ groaning ]

436
00:30:13,826 --> 00:30:15,126
[ spits ]

437
00:30:23,285 --> 00:30:25,420
Let's go.

438
00:30:26,205 --> 00:30:28,106
[ winces ]

439
00:30:43,122 --> 00:30:45,256
[ seabirds calling ]

440
00:30:53,632 --> 00:30:55,517
[ groaning ]

441
00:31:00,990 --> 00:31:03,124
No. No.

442
00:31:03,192 --> 00:31:04,209
Damn it.

443
00:31:05,711 --> 00:31:08,312
[ groans ]

444
00:31:08,381 --> 00:31:10,648
Why the hell
didn't they kill us?

445
00:31:12,651 --> 00:31:15,437
I don't know.

446
00:31:15,505 --> 00:31:17,472
Doesn't make sense.

447
00:31:21,810 --> 00:31:23,895
[ coughs ]

448
00:31:23,963 --> 00:31:25,797
Rich.
Yeah?

449
00:31:25,931 --> 00:31:27,081
Girl Sarge brought in

450
00:31:27,149 --> 00:31:28,583
was too far gone.

451
00:31:29,535 --> 00:31:30,819
Shit.

452
00:31:30,887 --> 00:31:32,053
We need a replacement,

453
00:31:32,121 --> 00:31:34,489
preferably one that's
not frickin' dead.

454
00:31:34,557 --> 00:31:37,325
Sarge, the dead girl
you brought us was obviously garbage.

455
00:31:37,393 --> 00:31:39,995
I need you to go back out there
and find somebody else,

456
00:31:40,062 --> 00:31:41,129
preferably in one piece.

457
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:42,748
We've already
been out there once

458
00:31:42,815 --> 00:31:44,282
to dump those idiots
on the island.

459
00:31:44,350 --> 00:31:46,785
Then go back out again now.

460
00:31:46,853 --> 00:31:48,052
Understood.

461
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:50,288
The people on that island,
their blood work is perfect.

462
00:31:50,355 --> 00:31:51,740
They've been handpicked.

463
00:31:51,807 --> 00:31:53,792
See, that's what we're
selling here is perfection.

464
00:31:53,859 --> 00:31:56,878
That's a little hard to do
when you beat the shit out of 'em!

465
00:31:56,945 --> 00:31:59,781
I mean it.
Not a scratch!

466
00:32:01,166 --> 00:32:04,402
Okay, guys, let's fall out.

467
00:32:04,470 --> 00:32:07,389
Xander, if Sarge and I
have a falling out,

468
00:32:07,456 --> 00:32:09,407
are you prepared to take over
the operation?

469
00:32:10,459 --> 00:32:12,210
What are you asking me?

470
00:32:12,277 --> 00:32:15,279
Not asking anything yet,
but I think you know what I mean.

471
00:32:25,073 --> 00:32:27,325
What did he want?

472
00:32:27,392 --> 00:32:29,393
He wanted to know what happened
to the girl.

473
00:32:29,462 --> 00:32:32,029
I said it was my fault,
I missed the shot.

474
00:32:32,097 --> 00:32:34,031
He told me not
to mess up again.

475
00:32:34,099 --> 00:32:35,517
What did you say to that?

476
00:32:35,585 --> 00:32:37,118
Well, I told him

477
00:32:37,186 --> 00:32:39,354
maybe if he thinks he could do
a better job,

478
00:32:39,422 --> 00:32:40,922
he should come along with us

479
00:32:40,990 --> 00:32:42,290
and take one out himself.

480
00:32:59,808 --> 00:33:03,611
You two go on. Not you.

481
00:33:06,282 --> 00:33:08,817
So you wanna take over, eh?

482
00:33:08,884 --> 00:33:10,151
No.

483
00:33:10,219 --> 00:33:11,937
Did he ask you to kill me?

484
00:33:12,004 --> 00:33:13,205
No.

485
00:33:13,272 --> 00:33:15,623
I don't believe you.

486
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:18,559
Let's go.

487
00:33:25,151 --> 00:33:26,484
[ grunts ]

488
00:33:26,552 --> 00:33:28,269
There's only room
for one leader here.

489
00:33:47,289 --> 00:33:49,690
[ brush rustling ]

490
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:39,674
[ blade slashes ]

491
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:49,767
[ steady whine ]

492
00:34:53,738 --> 00:34:55,673
[ whimpering ]

493
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:06,550
What's that?

494
00:35:06,618 --> 00:35:08,419
Think it's an ear.

495
00:35:08,437 --> 00:35:09,854
Yeah, I can see that.

496
00:35:09,921 --> 00:35:11,806
Oh, my God.

497
00:35:11,874 --> 00:35:13,407
[ sobs ]

498
00:35:13,475 --> 00:35:15,843
Oh, God.

499
00:35:15,911 --> 00:35:17,912
Oh, shit. Oh, my God.
She's going into shock.

500
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:19,246
Okay, we gotta
get back to camp.

501
00:35:19,314 --> 00:35:20,648
Oh, my God.
Come on.

502
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:24,535
If you take things
into your own hands again,

503
00:35:24,603 --> 00:35:26,621
that will be
your ear on that machete,

504
00:35:26,689 --> 00:35:29,040
and it won't be no accident.
You understand?

505
00:35:31,944 --> 00:35:33,010
What happened?

506
00:35:33,078 --> 00:35:34,579
They cut her ear off!

507
00:35:34,647 --> 00:35:35,380
What do we do?

508
00:35:35,447 --> 00:35:36,781
Put her here.
Put her here!

509
00:35:36,848 --> 00:35:38,416
Jean, get some firewood!

510
00:35:40,135 --> 00:35:41,252
I've got to cauterize this.

511
00:35:41,404 --> 00:35:43,037
Make a fire quick.
Hey!

512
00:35:43,105 --> 00:35:44,188
Where's Todd?

513
00:35:44,256 --> 00:35:45,423
He didn't make it.

514
00:35:46,041 --> 00:35:47,359
You happy now, Billie?

515
00:35:47,426 --> 00:35:49,344
They trusted you.

516
00:35:49,411 --> 00:35:51,595
All right,
we gotta keep her warm.

517
00:35:51,663 --> 00:35:52,430
Okay.

518
00:36:07,146 --> 00:36:09,664
[ brush rustles ]

519
00:36:11,817 --> 00:36:13,401
[ wings flap ]

520
00:37:09,024 --> 00:37:10,524
[ frogs croaking ]

521
00:37:10,726 --> 00:37:13,677
Okay, tonight we're gonna swim
back to the island.

522
00:37:13,745 --> 00:37:14,929
Why?

523
00:37:15,497 --> 00:37:16,714
I mean,
there must be

524
00:37:16,782 --> 00:37:18,549
some method to their
madness. I mean,

525
00:37:18,617 --> 00:37:20,385
why would they just bring us
back here

526
00:37:20,452 --> 00:37:21,252
to hunt us down again?

527
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:24,622
A sociological experiment?

528
00:37:24,689 --> 00:37:28,475
Some sick human hunting game
for rich people?

529
00:37:29,812 --> 00:37:30,878
I don't know.

530
00:37:44,393 --> 00:37:49,847
I have a sister...

531
00:37:49,914 --> 00:37:51,382
Rina.

532
00:37:54,119 --> 00:37:56,137
We've always been different.

533
00:37:56,205 --> 00:37:57,671
She took after our mother,

534
00:37:57,739 --> 00:38:01,609
liked girlie things, shopping.

535
00:38:01,676 --> 00:38:04,495
Not me.

536
00:38:04,563 --> 00:38:05,830
I was Daddy's girl.

537
00:38:05,897 --> 00:38:07,481
Hold that jab.
He was a judo champion

538
00:38:07,549 --> 00:38:09,233
back in the Soviet Union

539
00:38:09,301 --> 00:38:11,886
and an officer in the Army.

540
00:38:11,954 --> 00:38:13,738
Jab, right cross.
Follow with that right cross.

541
00:38:13,806 --> 00:38:16,424
He started training me
as early as I can remember.

542
00:38:16,491 --> 00:38:18,543
That's it. Go deep.
That's it.

543
