809
00:50:38,400 --> 00:50:41,251
Won't let you down.

810
00:50:48,342 --> 00:50:51,545
Walsh, prep the girl
from yesterday.

811
00:50:51,612 --> 00:50:54,381
Screw Mao. She's not
gonna know the difference.

812
00:50:57,602 --> 00:51:00,787
What about that girl
on the island?

813
00:51:01,705 --> 00:51:03,140
I-I'll have them kill her.

814
00:51:03,207 --> 00:51:05,392
She wasn't brought here
for her blood work anyway.

815
00:51:05,460 --> 00:51:07,361
She was asking around
about me,

816
00:51:07,428 --> 00:51:09,479
specifically me.

817
00:51:09,547 --> 00:51:11,732
I just had her put here
so I could find out

818
00:51:11,799 --> 00:51:13,534
who she's working with
and what she knows.

819
00:51:13,601 --> 00:51:15,435
I thought it would be
a good idea

820
00:51:15,503 --> 00:51:16,871
to put her with
a sympathetic ear,

821
00:51:16,938 --> 00:51:19,073
but Quentin has apparently
dropped the ball on that.

822
00:51:19,140 --> 00:51:21,075
I'm not sure
what to do with her.

823
00:51:23,678 --> 00:51:27,330
I think you should do what
you feel's right.

824
00:51:29,384 --> 00:51:31,235
That's my girl.

825
00:51:36,424 --> 00:51:38,309
[ monitor beeping ]

826
00:52:13,277 --> 00:52:14,428
Hey.

827
00:52:24,338 --> 00:52:26,673
[ groaning ]

828
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:31,395
[ blade slices ]

829
00:52:34,632 --> 00:52:38,351
All right.
We'll have to be quick about this.

830
00:52:39,153 --> 00:52:41,071
NICK:
Too heavy, Stitch.

831
00:52:41,139 --> 00:52:41,822
BILLIE:
Am I hurting you?

832
00:52:41,890 --> 00:52:43,490
No. Am I hurting you?
No.

833
00:52:43,558 --> 00:52:45,626
What the hell
is going on here?

834
00:52:45,693 --> 00:52:49,246
Put her down!
Put her down now!

835
00:52:54,368 --> 00:52:55,802
Is that you, Nick?

836
00:52:58,822 --> 00:53:01,892
[ laughing ]

837
00:53:04,812 --> 00:53:06,563
You're with them!

838
00:53:06,630 --> 00:53:07,480
No, but you are.

839
00:53:07,682 --> 00:53:09,966
All along,
you were with them!

840
00:53:10,034 --> 00:53:11,201
Oh, come on. Stop it!

841
00:53:11,269 --> 00:53:12,218
We see right through you.

842
00:53:12,570 --> 00:53:15,155
Back up!
Just stay away!

843
00:53:15,222 --> 00:53:16,139
Back up!

844
00:53:19,076 --> 00:53:20,510
You see nothing.

845
00:53:30,705 --> 00:53:34,091
It's gonna be tough
going up against them.

846
00:53:37,044 --> 00:53:38,178
Good luck.

847
00:53:38,246 --> 00:53:39,913
[ laughs ]

848
00:53:39,981 --> 00:53:42,315
I'm outta here.

849
00:53:42,383 --> 00:53:44,734
<i>Sayonara!</i>

850
00:53:44,802 --> 00:53:45,635
[ laughs ]

851
00:54:40,090 --> 00:54:41,108
[ groans ]

852
00:54:44,279 --> 00:54:47,581
Okay, guys, this is
do or die for us.

853
00:54:47,648 --> 00:54:49,199
We have to take that boat,

854
00:54:49,266 --> 00:54:50,567
no matter who we meet,

855
00:54:50,635 --> 00:54:52,635
no matter what
we encounter, okay?

856
00:54:52,703 --> 00:54:54,304
We will.

857
00:54:54,372 --> 00:54:56,489
Okay, let's go.

858
00:55:40,267 --> 00:55:41,001
Shh.

859
00:55:55,950 --> 00:55:57,267
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

860
00:55:57,335 --> 00:55:58,502
Don't move.

861
00:56:06,694 --> 00:56:08,762
BILLIE:
You guys can have the boat.

862
00:56:08,830 --> 00:56:11,164
Go wherever you want.
You're free now.

863
00:56:12,300 --> 00:56:14,434
But first,
you're dropping me off.

864
00:56:14,502 --> 00:56:15,702
NICK:
Are you crazy?

865
00:56:15,770 --> 00:56:16,803
I'm not going anywhere

866
00:56:16,954 --> 00:56:19,088
without finding out
what's going on here.

867
00:56:19,156 --> 00:56:22,158
So there's no way we
could change your mind?

868
00:56:23,244 --> 00:56:25,495
Not on this.

869
00:56:25,563 --> 00:56:26,546
Seriously?

870
00:56:26,614 --> 00:56:29,833
You have that low
of an opinion of me?

871
00:56:31,469 --> 00:56:33,687
What about you, Stitch?

872
00:56:33,754 --> 00:56:35,856
What am I supposed
to say, eh?

873
00:56:36,023 --> 00:56:37,490
We made it this far,
didn't we?

874
00:56:37,558 --> 00:56:39,226
[ laughs ]

875
00:56:39,294 --> 00:56:40,960
Be rude not to, really.

876
00:56:41,028 --> 00:56:42,079
[ laughs ]

877
00:56:42,230 --> 00:56:43,497
Thank you.

878
00:56:49,654 --> 00:56:52,855
What's
our operational status?

879
00:56:52,874 --> 00:56:54,625
Surgery on Song Mao
is under way now.

880
00:56:54,692 --> 00:56:57,210
And the, uh, mission
to the island?

881
00:56:57,277 --> 00:56:59,679
No report yet.

882
00:57:00,531 --> 00:57:03,083
I'll be in me quarters
if you need me.

883
00:57:07,388 --> 00:57:09,689
[ overlapping chatter
in Spanish ]

884
00:57:19,416 --> 00:57:22,119
Well, hello there,
little lady.

885
00:57:22,186 --> 00:57:23,219
[ gasps ]

886
00:57:27,908 --> 00:57:31,111
You want a job working on
a private island?

887
00:57:57,638 --> 00:57:59,222
We've got complications.

888
00:58:06,263 --> 00:58:08,098
What?

889
00:58:10,334 --> 00:58:13,119
She's had the Kasha procedure,
hasn't she?

890
00:58:15,706 --> 00:58:18,525
Well, it's resulted in
biliary atresia.

891
00:58:18,593 --> 00:58:20,393
RICH:
Speak English.

892
00:58:20,461 --> 00:58:21,894
Her bile duct
isn't functioning.

893
00:58:21,962 --> 00:58:24,297
I don't know if
the new liver'll help.

894
00:58:27,168 --> 00:58:29,235
And I don't care
what you have to do, Walsh.

895
00:58:29,303 --> 00:58:31,671
You get back in there right now,
and you save her.

896
00:58:31,739 --> 00:58:33,006
Yeah, I will,

897
00:58:33,074 --> 00:58:34,557
but we've gotta be prepared to--

898
00:58:34,625 --> 00:58:35,842
Walsh, fix it!

899
00:58:35,910 --> 00:58:38,178
You want to
come up here and do it?!

900
00:58:43,367 --> 00:58:45,201
[ gasps ]

901
00:58:45,269 --> 00:58:47,637
I came...

902
00:59:03,554 --> 00:59:06,906
Doesn't look like the dock's
guarded, you know.

903
00:59:08,125 --> 00:59:10,143
Yeah, well, there might be
some people around the house.

904
00:59:12,229 --> 00:59:14,263
What are we waiting for?

905
00:59:18,569 --> 00:59:21,137
Hey, guys, wait!
Stop! Stop.

906
00:59:22,890 --> 00:59:26,410
Look, uh,

907
00:59:26,477 --> 00:59:28,645
I've got
an admission to make.

908
00:59:31,014 --> 00:59:32,932
I'm not in the S.A.S.

909
00:59:34,885 --> 00:59:36,803
I mean,
I went for special ops.

910
00:59:36,871 --> 00:59:40,757
Just that, well, I got washed out
of their training program.

911
00:59:41,893 --> 00:59:43,526
I mean, I'm military.

912
00:59:43,594 --> 00:59:46,162
Heh. Well,
did the basic training.

913
00:59:46,230 --> 00:59:50,783
It's just that I'm not
like those guys out there.

914
00:59:51,418 --> 00:59:54,353
They're trained killers.

915
00:59:55,740 --> 00:59:57,907
You weren't taken into a
battlefield hospital?

916
00:59:59,627 --> 01:00:01,027
No.

917
01:00:01,229 --> 01:00:03,012
Oh, I mean,
I was hospitalized,

918
01:00:03,080 --> 01:00:05,599
but not
from the front line.

919
01:00:06,634 --> 01:00:08,101
I got food poisoning.

920
01:00:09,536 --> 01:00:11,121
I work
in the mess hall.

921
01:00:12,890 --> 01:00:14,758
What about Afghanistan,
the two times wounded?

922
01:00:14,825 --> 01:00:16,225
Didn't you say that?

923
01:00:17,662 --> 01:00:20,129
But you've been
in combat before, right?

924
01:00:21,281 --> 01:00:23,700
Before today, no.

925
01:00:23,767 --> 01:00:25,585
Heh. Great.

926
01:00:25,653 --> 01:00:27,170
I knew something was up

927
01:00:27,238 --> 01:00:29,823
when you said how long you
were on the island.

928
01:00:29,890 --> 01:00:33,026
A Special Ops soldier
on an island for 44 days?

929
01:00:33,094 --> 01:00:35,728
Two months?
Doing what? Nothing?

930
01:00:37,198 --> 01:00:38,698
Sorry.

931
01:00:39,666 --> 01:00:41,117
[ sighs ]
Look, Stitch,

932
01:00:41,185 --> 01:00:44,020
you can stay here with the boat
if you want to, okay?

933
01:00:44,088 --> 01:00:46,222
Nick, you're coming
with me, right?

934
01:00:48,258 --> 01:00:53,079
We'll come back for you, okay?

935
01:00:54,248 --> 01:00:55,398
No, no, no.

936
01:00:55,466 --> 01:00:57,400
Wait, wait, wait.
Just wait.

937
01:00:57,468 --> 01:00:58,050
[ sighs ]

938
01:00:58,118 --> 01:01:00,219
Look, if it
wasn't for you guys,

939
01:01:00,404 --> 01:01:03,606
we'd still be stuck
on that island, right?

940
01:01:05,159 --> 01:01:07,927
I owe you guys my life.

941
01:01:08,963 --> 01:01:11,381
I'm coming, all right?
I'm coming.

942
01:01:53,340 --> 01:01:55,792
[ exhales ]

943
01:01:55,860 --> 01:01:56,926
On the count of three.

944
01:01:56,994 --> 01:01:58,845
Okay.
Okay.

945
01:01:58,912 --> 01:02:01,263
1, 2, 3.

946
01:02:03,734 --> 01:02:05,251
Just give me a minute.

947
01:02:08,222 --> 01:02:09,405
[ grunts ]

948
01:02:15,947 --> 01:02:17,296
[ neck cracks ]

949
01:02:36,750 --> 01:02:38,835
[ flies buzzing ]

950
01:02:47,344 --> 01:02:48,395
Clear.

951
01:02:51,432 --> 01:02:52,915
[ coughs ]

952
01:03:07,531 --> 01:03:09,565
[ gasping ]

953
01:03:29,503 --> 01:03:31,587
Oh, my God.

954
01:03:42,015 --> 01:03:44,166
It's Jean.

955
01:03:48,505 --> 01:03:50,439
Holy shit.

956
01:03:53,143 --> 01:03:56,045
They're organ thieves.

957
01:03:56,113 --> 01:03:58,915
They're harvesting us

958
01:03:58,983 --> 01:04:01,250
for this, our organs.

959
01:04:05,773 --> 01:04:07,524
An organ farm.

960
01:04:31,182 --> 01:04:33,165
Where's Sarge?

961
01:04:33,250 --> 01:04:35,585
ANNOUNCER:
20,000 Polish fans

962
01:04:35,653 --> 01:04:37,119
are packed into Wembley.

963
01:04:37,187 --> 01:04:39,239
It's an electric atmosphere.

964
01:04:39,306 --> 01:04:41,524
[ radio continues indistinctly ]

965
01:04:46,863 --> 01:04:48,514
Well back.

966
01:04:48,582 --> 01:04:49,732
He's falling in.

967
01:04:49,800 --> 01:04:51,317
[ continues indistinctly ]

968
01:04:52,069 --> 01:04:53,853
That was an excellent move

969
01:04:53,921 --> 01:04:55,855
by Wayne to get it down.

970
01:04:55,923 --> 01:04:57,289
It takes you there.

971
01:04:57,357 --> 01:04:59,675
There's a chance
to break out here.

972
01:04:59,827 --> 01:05:00,960
Taking it across here.

973
01:05:01,028 --> 01:05:02,712
Hits the bar! No!

974
01:05:02,779 --> 01:05:04,380
Ah, into the side netting.

975
01:05:05,432 --> 01:05:07,233
Reporting for England there.

976
01:05:07,301 --> 01:05:10,253
Look at the space.
In the clear.

977
01:05:10,320 --> 01:05:13,873
Once again, Poland looking
to counterattack here.

978
01:05:13,940 --> 01:05:15,841
Oh, it's been left beautifully.

979
01:05:15,909 --> 01:05:17,927
Lewandowski into the area,

980
01:05:17,995 --> 01:05:20,496
and he's pulled his shot wide.

981
01:05:20,564 --> 01:05:22,832
He can barely believe it.

982
01:05:22,900 --> 01:05:26,268
[ continues indistinctly ]

983
01:05:26,336 --> 01:05:28,070
England stretched at the back.

984
01:05:28,139 --> 01:05:30,706
Townsend on the charge.

985
01:05:30,774 --> 01:05:32,425
Smalling is offside here.

986
01:05:32,493 --> 01:05:33,876
Here's the ball back.
Way to go.

987
01:05:33,944 --> 01:05:35,444
And it's Townsend.

988
01:05:35,512 --> 01:05:36,345
Hits the bar!

989
01:05:36,413 --> 01:05:38,197
[ continues indistinctly ]

990
01:05:38,265 --> 01:05:40,299
Ball straight to the keeper.

991
01:05:40,367 --> 01:05:43,986
Ah, England highly
under pressure.

992
01:05:44,054 --> 01:05:46,222
And with Townsend
rattling the crossbar.

993
01:05:46,290 --> 01:05:48,858
Sturridge on the follow.

994
01:05:48,926 --> 01:05:50,893
[ continues indistinctly ]

995
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:54,580
Oh, Sturridge!

996
01:05:54,648 --> 01:05:55,732
It goes wide!

997
01:05:55,799 --> 01:05:56,933
They fall back.

998
01:05:57,001 --> 01:05:59,035
What an unbelievable miss.

999
01:06:00,203 --> 01:06:02,021
Sturridge right to left,

1000
01:06:02,088 --> 01:06:04,573
goes right instead,

1001
01:06:04,641 --> 01:06:06,325
drives down the middle.

1002
01:06:06,393 --> 01:06:07,760
Ball in under pressure here.

1003
01:06:07,828 --> 01:06:09,912
Ah, it's left of beam.

1004
01:06:09,980 --> 01:06:11,597
It's Wayne Rooney!

1005
01:06:11,665 --> 01:06:13,366
England takes the lead!

1006
01:06:13,433 --> 01:06:16,686
And Wembley breathes
a sigh of relief.

1007
01:06:16,687 --> 01:06:19,421
Beautiful ball in for Wayne.

1008
01:06:21,408 --> 01:06:23,142
[ continues indistinctly ]

1009
01:06:23,210 --> 01:06:24,593
[ door clicks ]

1010
01:06:35,638 --> 01:06:37,557
[ gasps ]

1011
01:06:37,625 --> 01:06:39,291
[ sobs ]

1012
01:06:43,813 --> 01:06:46,032
[ footsteps clattering ]

1013
01:06:53,757 --> 01:06:54,924
[ door opens ]

1014
01:06:54,992 --> 01:06:57,177
[ monitor whining ]

1015
01:07:01,899 --> 01:07:04,283
[ crying ]

1016
01:07:08,789 --> 01:07:11,574
Shh.

1017
01:07:55,703 --> 01:07:57,219
Whoa! Whoa!

1018
01:07:57,321 --> 01:07:59,339
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

1019
01:07:59,406 --> 01:08:00,305
We can work this out!

1020
01:08:00,591 --> 01:08:03,026
Just hold on!
Wait! One moment!

1021
01:08:03,093 --> 01:08:05,011
[ Rich yelling ]

1022
01:08:05,079 --> 01:08:05,811
[ gunshot ]

1023
01:08:05,879 --> 01:08:07,597
Stop! No! Stop!

1024
01:08:17,124 --> 01:08:19,392
RICH:
Wait, okay? Hold on!

1025
01:08:19,459 --> 01:08:21,560
We can settle this now.

1026
01:08:21,628 --> 01:08:22,795
Hold on!

1027
01:08:32,622 --> 01:08:33,790
Stop.

1028
01:08:35,893 --> 01:08:37,659
[ gasps ]

1029
01:08:51,725 --> 01:08:55,327
Mao, it is this woman's fault
right here.

1030
01:08:55,395 --> 01:08:57,597
Our first two donors
died because of her.

1031
01:08:57,665 --> 01:09:00,533
Your daughter would still be alive
right now if it weren't for her!

1032
01:09:00,600 --> 01:09:04,203
Lies!
You stole my sister.

1033
01:09:04,270 --> 01:09:06,105
You are the cause of this.

1034
01:09:06,172 --> 01:09:09,175
You're pathetic.
Hold on.

1035
01:09:11,528 --> 01:09:13,713
Allow me
to eliminate her for you.

1036
01:09:18,986 --> 01:09:20,669
No!

1037
01:09:20,737 --> 01:09:22,154
No!

1038
01:09:22,222 --> 01:09:23,890
[ yelling ]

1039
01:09:31,348 --> 01:09:32,381
[ gunfire ]

1040
01:09:32,449 --> 01:09:33,899
Just what England
needed at the moment.

1041
01:09:39,539 --> 01:09:41,540
Fucking stuck.

1042
01:09:42,726 --> 01:09:44,059
Oh, my God.
You've been shot.

1043
01:09:44,127 --> 01:09:45,628
[ gunfire continues ]

1044
01:09:49,433 --> 01:09:51,350
Go, go, go!

1045
01:09:51,418 --> 01:09:53,486
STITCH:
Go on. Let's get out of here!

1046
01:10:03,329 --> 01:10:05,314
[ gunfire continues nearby ]

1047
01:10:06,065 --> 01:10:07,533
Okay, clear!

1048
01:10:19,496 --> 01:10:20,713
[ blows ]

1049
01:10:31,908 --> 01:10:33,492
Oh, shit.

1050
01:10:39,466 --> 01:10:40,616
[ groaning ]

1051
01:10:46,890 --> 01:10:47,907
Ah, shit.

1052
01:10:47,975 --> 01:10:50,276
[ gasping ]

1053
01:10:50,343 --> 01:10:52,495
[ gunfire continues nearby ]

1054
01:10:57,767 --> 01:10:59,968
Kat!

1055
01:11:00,036 --> 01:11:01,670
You're dead!

1056
01:11:01,738 --> 01:11:03,672
You betrayed me!

1057
01:11:11,464 --> 01:11:12,698
[ clicks ]

1058
01:11:29,816 --> 01:11:31,767
[ gunfire echoing ]

1059
01:11:57,144 --> 01:11:58,710
Oi!

1060
01:12:09,005 --> 01:12:10,239
Ah, shit. I'm out.

1061
01:12:11,875 --> 01:12:14,309
Billie, you take Nick
and your sister.

1062
01:12:14,377 --> 01:12:15,861
Get 'em out of here.

1063
01:12:15,929 --> 01:12:17,129
You sure?

1064
01:12:17,197 --> 01:12:19,131
Yeah, just go.

1065
01:12:39,402 --> 01:12:42,021
[ yelling ]

1066
01:13:08,899 --> 01:13:10,432
[ gasps ]

1067
01:13:12,502 --> 01:13:14,102
[ coughs ]

1068
01:13:14,170 --> 01:13:16,004
[ Nick panting ]

1069
01:13:22,845 --> 01:13:25,431
Billie, what are you doing here?
How did you even find me?

1070
01:13:25,499 --> 01:13:27,283
What do you mean?

1071
01:13:27,350 --> 01:13:29,184
I never stopped looking for you.

1072
01:13:29,252 --> 01:13:32,571
I've been searching all over
the world for you for five years.

1073
01:13:32,638 --> 01:13:34,490
Well, you should have stayed away.

1074
01:13:34,558 --> 01:13:37,259
I'm no good.
You know Dad always said that.

1075
01:13:37,327 --> 01:13:39,779
Katerina, Dad's gone.

1076
01:13:39,846 --> 01:13:41,664
It's just you and me now.

1077
01:13:41,732 --> 01:13:44,633
And I don't care what he said.

1078
01:13:44,701 --> 01:13:46,602
You know he didn't mean it.

1079
